From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0800
Subject: Spoof WebGL vendor/renderer strings for GPU anti-fingerprinting

Under PureCloak, replace the WebGL GL_VENDOR, GL_RENDERER,
UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL, and UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL strings with
deterministic fake values generated by the PureCloak PRNG. This prevents
WebGL fingerprinting from leaking actual GPU hardware info.

The spoofed vendor and renderer strings are selected from realistic sets
(e.g., "Google Inc.", "Intel", "NVIDIA Corporation" for vendor; ANGLE
renderer strings matching common configurations for renderer). The
selection is deterministic per workspace seed, so different workspaces
produce different (but always realistic) GPU strings.

No BUILDFLAG guards are needed since patches only apply during
PureCloak builds.

---
